{"cite_id": "cite-1", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "the perfection of His purity is to deny Him attributes—for every attribute stands as evidence that it differs from that which it describes", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler, 4th century AH)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-2", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "whoever attaches attributes to Allah recognizes His like", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-3", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "He is Being itself, but not through process of becoming. He exists, but not from non-existence. He is present with all things, yet not through physical proximity.", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-4", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "He assigned to all things their times, brought together their variations, established their properties, and determined their forms, knowing them before they were created", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-5", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "Among them are those immersed in prostration, never rising. Others are bowed in kneeling, never standing upright.", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-6", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "From this he formed a figure—marked with joints, articulations, limbs, and segments. He hardened it until it dried completely for an appointed term and known duration. Then He breathed into it of His Spirit", "source_work": "Nahj al-Balagha", "source_author": "Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib", "source_authority": "al-Sharif al-Radi (compiler)", "source_location_hint": "Sermon 1 (Khutbat al-Bayan)", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-7", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "Be prostrate toward Adam, and they prostrated, save Iblis.", "source_work": "Qur'an", "source_author": "Divine Revelation", "source_authority": "Qur'anic canon", "source_location_hint": "2:34; also 7:11, 18:50", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
{"cite_id": "cite-8", "section_id": 3598, "section_position": 1, "excerpt": "Verily, thou shalt be among the respited until the Day of the Known Time.", "source_work": "Qur'an", "source_author": "Divine Revelation", "source_authority": "Qur'anic canon", "source_location_hint": "15:38; also 38:81", "confidence": "high", "training_grounded": true}
